title: Pa. boys and girls: Wood, Ryan keep rolling
text:
Elsewhere in the Catholic League, Joan Kuneck scored in overtime as host Hallahan topped Cardinal O'Hara, 2-1. Field Hockey Abbey Butler scored a pair of goals as Central Bucks East beat host Pennridge, 4-2, in the Suburban One Continental. Boys' Soccer Michael Gamain scored in double overtime as host Perkiomen School beat Renaissance Academy, 3-2, in the Tri-County League. Football Casey Williams ran 32 times for 181 yards and two touchdowns and Martell Marshall ran for 94 more yards as visiting Southern topped Fels, 22-0, in Public League AAAA Liberty action.
Public AAA. Tarell Mcleod ran for 159 yards and the winning TD in West Philadelphia's 20-14 victory over Dobbins at Simon Gratz.
